The atmosphere is perfect for a night out. Small tables for an intimate dining experience with companions and perfect mood lighting that is not too dark but not too light.

For the food, my date and I had the Burger, Ribs, and Mozzarella Sticks:
Ribs: Pretty good! The rub and spice on it was just the right amount to dance on the tip of the tongue and very flavorful.
Burger: Smash burger, was overcooked (but that's often the case with smash burgers), had a weird spice/taste to it. Probably not worth the purchase unless you like your burgers cooked well-done. The fries that came with it are standard fare, needed more salt though.
Mozzarella Sticks: The cheese has a decent taste to it, but the breading is just a little too thick and ends up tasting a little bland.

I'll definitely be coming back though to try some other stuff because the ribs were enough to keep my date and I curious about the rest of the menu! :)

AMAZING PLACE! From the moment we stepped into Cousin Larry‚Äôs, we were greeted with a warmth and hospitality that made us feel like longtime friends. The staff goes above and beyond to make every guest feel welcome and well cared for, creating an inviting atmosphere that made our visit even more enjoyable.

The handcrafted margaritas, made with fresh ingredients, was a standout! We opted for the brunch special, which included bottomless margaritas at a great value! The pancakes, sausage, and eggs were delicious, with the maple syrup butter bringing them over the top. The breakfast burger, served with crispy French fries, was both flavorful and cooked to perfection.

We enjoyed ourselves so much that we decided to stay through dinner, where we had the opportunity to try the beef stew‚Äîit was absolutely phenomenal. The flavors were rich and comforting, making it the highlight of the evening. Chef‚Äôs kiss!

We also had mozzarella sticks and cheesecake, which we devoured so quickly that we forgot to get any photos! üòÇ Both were fantastic.

Overall, Cousin Larry‚Äôs exceeded expectations in every way. The combination of delicious food, excellent service, and a welcoming ambiance makes it a place I highly recommend. Whether you‚Äôre stopping by for brunch, dinner, or just a drink, you won‚Äôt be disappointed.

Came in on an ice-cold weekday night, and were quickly placed into a cozy corner nook. Initial service was fast, and overall the vibe was warm, and not terribly noisy despite there being a couple other tables and the bar occupied.

Ordered basic drinks to start, pricing here is good -- and the happy hour specials are pretty solid. Dinner menu is deceptively basic. Traditional pub fare as is the Sunnyside Irish way -- but elevated and delicious in a way that I was not expecting. Had the half chicken which was flavorful, with crispy skin and well cooked. Nice portion size with well roasted root vegetables & potato with gravy. My guest had a burger (with surprise gluten free bun, gotta love it!) and it disappeared in an instant

To top it off, our waiter was very friendly, good at his job, and seemed genuinely excited about the restaurant. I am too, and we'll be back.
